      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:  The article about movie titles "It's Right on the Tip of Your Tongue"  [ March 5 ]  explored a subject that many who have worked in the industry have tussled with, too.</p>
        <p>When I was a kid writer at Warner Brothers, Brynie Foy, who churned out 25 B pictures a year, put it as intelligently and succinctly as anyone: "Turhan Bey and Toby Wing in 'South of Suez' is sure a lousy title. But Clark Cable and Hedy Lamarr in 'South of Suez' is a hell of a title." ROBERT BLEES Los Angeles  MOVIE TITLES</p>
      </block>
